            "content": "[![Chatroom Gitter](https://img.shields.io/badge/Chatroom-Gitter-%23753a88)](https://gitter.im/haskell-nix/Lobby)\n[![Hackage](https://img.shields.io/hackage/v/hnix?color=%235e5086&label=Latest%20release%20on%20Hackage)](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/hnix)\n[![Hackage Matrix Builder](https://img.shields.io/badge/Hackage%20Matrix-Builder-%235e5086)](https://matrix.hackage.haskell.org/package/hnix)\n[![Bounds](https://img.shields.io/hackage-deps/v/hnix?label=Released%20dep%20bounds)](https://packdeps.haskellers.com/feed?needle=hnix)\n[![Hydra CI](https://img.shields.io/badge/Nixpkgs%20Hydra-CI-%234f72bb)](https://hydra.nixos.org/job/nixpkgs/trunk/haskellPackages.hnix.x86_64-linux#tabs-status)\n[![Repology page](https://img.shields.io/badge/Repology-page-%23005500)](https://repology.org/project/haskell:hnix/versions)\n\n\n# HNix\n\nHNix is a Haskell implementation of the Nix expression language -- a parser,\nevaluator, and type checker built using recursion schemes and abstract\ndefinitional interpreters. I've been working on it since 2014, and the main\ngoal right now is to be able to evaluate all of Nixpkgs.\n\nWe're not there yet, but we're getting closer.\n\n\n## Building\n\nYou'll need Nix installed, since HNix still relies on `nix-shell` and\n`nix-store` for some operations.\n\n**A word of caution**: the `derivationStrict` primOp creates real `/nix/store`\nentries through `hnix-store-remote` and the running `nix-daemon`. It's\neffectful -- be aware of that when experimenting.\n\n```shell\ngit clone https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix.git && cd hnix\nnix develop       # enter the development shell\ncabal v2-configure\ncabal v2-build\n```\n\n### Running tests\n\n```shell\ncabal v2-test                           # default suite\nenv ALL_TESTS=yes cabal v2-test         # everything\nenv NIXPKGS_TESTS=yes cabal v2-test     # nixpkgs compatibility\nenv PRETTY_TESTS=1 cabal v2-test        # pretty-printer round-trips\n```\n\n### Using Nix directly\n\nThere's a `default.nix` with a number of build options that pass through the\n[Nixpkgs Haskell Lib API](https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/blob/master/pkgs/development/haskell-modules/lib.nix).\nYou can also just run `nix build` to build via the flake.\n\n\n## Usage\n\n```shell\nhnix file.nix                              # parse and pretty-print\nhnix --eval file.nix                       # evaluate a file\nhnix --eval --expr 'import <nixpkgs> {}'   # evaluate an expression\nhnix --repl                                # interactive REPL\n```\n\nRun `hnix --help` for the full set of options.\n\n### Things only HNix can do\n\n```shell\n# Value provenance and thunk context\nhnix -v2 --values --thunk --eval --expr 'import <nixpkgs> {}'\n\n# Evaluation tracing\nhnix --trace --eval --expr 'import <nixpkgs> {}'\n\n# Test case reduction -- handy for narrowing down evaluation bugs\nhnix --reduce bug.nix --eval --expr 'import <nixpkgs> {}'\n```\n\n### REPL\n\n```shell\nhnix --repl\nhnix --eval --expr '(import <nixpkgs> {}).pkgs.hello' --repl\n```\n\nThe second form evaluates the expression first and binds the result to `input`,\nso you can inspect it interactively. Use `:help` for available commands.\n\nNix is lazy, so by default you'll see `\"<expr>\"` for unevaluated thunks. Add\n`--strict` (or `:set strict` in the REPL) to force full evaluation.\n\n\n## Development\n\nThe development shell (`nix develop`) includes cabal, HLS, hlint, fourmolu,\nshellcheck, shfmt, and lefthook. HLS works well with this project.\n\n### Pre-commit hooks\n\nWe use [Lefthook](https://github.com/evilmartians/lefthook) for pre-commit\nchecks:\n\n```shell\nlefthook install\n```\n\nThis runs formatting checks (fourmolu, shfmt), linting (hlint, shellcheck),\nand the build and test suite before each commit -- all in parallel.\n\n### Formatting\n\nAll Haskell code is formatted with [fourmolu](https://github.com/fourmolu/fourmolu).\nTo format the entire codebase:\n\n```shell\nfind src main tests benchmarks -name '*.hs' -exec fourmolu --mode inplace {} +\n```\n\nShell scripts are formatted with [shfmt](https://github.com/mvdan/sh):\n\n```shell\nshfmt -w build.sh\n```\n\n### Benchmarks and profiling\n\n```shell\ncabal v2-bench    # run criterion benchmarks\n```\n\nFor profiling, GHC's\n[profiling guide](https://ghc.gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/doc/users_guide/profiling.html)\ncovers the details. Here's a quick example:\n\n```shell\ncabal v2-run --enable-profiling --flags=profiling \\\n  --enable-library-profiling --profiling-detail='all-functions' \\\n  hnix -- --eval --expr '(import <nixpkgs> {}).firefox.outPath' +RTS -Pj\n```\n\nUpload the resulting `hnix.prof` to [speedscope.app](https://speedscope.app/)\nfor visualization.\n\n### Full debug info\n\n```shell\ncabal v2-configure --enable-tests --enable-profiling \\\n  --flags=profiling --flags=tracing\ncabal v2-run hnix -- -v5 --trace <args> +RTS -xc\n```\n\n\n## Contributing\n\nIf something in the [open issues](https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3A%22help+wanted%22+no%3Aassignee)\nlooks interesting, leave a comment to let others know you're working on it.\nYou're welcome to chat with everyone on [Gitter](https://gitter.im/haskell-nix/Lobby).\n\nBefore submitting a PR, please run `cabal v2-test` and make sure all\npreviously-passing tests still pass. It's OK if no new tests are passing.\n\n\n## Project status\n\n  * [ChangeLog](https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix/blob/master/ChangeLog.md)\n  * [Open issues](https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix/issues)\n  * [Project status wiki](https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix/wiki/Project-status)\n  * [Design of the HNix code base](https://github.com/haskell-nix/hnix/wiki/Design-of-the-HNix-code-base)\n",
